    <briefdescription>
<para>Describes input filtering rules for text input. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is a value-type object used to configure which input characters are allowed or denied.</para>
<para>The allow pattern defines input that can be inserted. If it is set, input that does not match the allow pattern is rejected.</para>
<para>The deny pattern defines input that cannot be inserted. If it is set, input that matches the deny pattern is rejected.</para>
<para>If both patterns are set, input must match the allow pattern and must not match the deny pattern. Input is rejected if it does not match the allow pattern, or if it matches the deny pattern.</para>
<para>The patterns follow std::regex ECMAScript grammar. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
